"When I say that Grinnell is a
great college, I do not mean to
imply that it is without prob-
lems. Obviously, we coma use
more money. Some new build-
ings are needed. According to
several articles in the Scarlet
and Black, the students might
be more interested in campus
affairs. The word “apathy" ape
peered several times. Doubt.
less, if I asked faculty mem-
bers, they would tell me that
